EFF leader Julius Malema has reacted to the final state capture inquiry report released last week, saying it is “gossip” and that chief justice Raymond Zondo “wasted” R2bn as chair of the inquiry. Malema said the EFF is the rightful replacement of the ANC and  the red berets would make education compulsory. TimesLIVE Support independent journalism by subscribing to the Sunday Times. Just R20 for the first month.